DA leader Mmusi Maimane at the party's final rally in Soweto on 4 May 2019. JOHANNESBURG - Democratic Alliance leader Mmusi Maimane is in the clear. The DA's financial committee has cleared Maimane of any wrongdoing. READ: Maimane wants probe into car and house allegations Maimane found himself in a sticky situation as news came out of the Steinhoff-sponsored car he used and the Cape Town house he is currently renting. In a statement, DA finance chairperson and MP Dion George said it was Maimane who had referred the matter to the finance committee for investigation after numerous anonymous leaks.